1
00:00:02,206 --> 00:00:04,137
Once upon a Christmas,

2
00:00:04,206 --> 00:00:07,137
Santa and Mrs. Claus
lived happily at the north pole

3
00:00:07,206 --> 00:00:09,000
with their two daughters,

4
00:00:09,068 --> 00:00:13,586
rudolfa, who was naughty,
and Kristin, who was nice...

5
00:00:13,655 --> 00:00:15,310
But all was not well.

6
00:00:15,379 --> 00:00:18,103
Santa, fearing that people
had lost the Christmas spirit,

7
00:00:18,172 --> 00:00:20,379
was making plans to retire,

8
00:00:20,448 --> 00:00:22,310
and rudolfa, seeing her chance,

9
00:00:22,379 --> 00:00:25,379
hatched a plan
to ruin Christmas forever,

10
00:00:25,448 --> 00:00:27,551
and she almost did,

11
00:00:27,620 --> 00:00:30,137
until Kristin saved the day,

12
00:00:30,206 --> 00:00:31,344
resurrecting Santa's hope

13
00:00:31,413 --> 00:00:32,793
by getting a mortal family

14
00:00:32,862 --> 00:00:35,448
to embrace
the true spirit of Christmas,

15
00:00:35,517 --> 00:00:37,137
and, along the way,

16
00:00:37,206 --> 00:00:38,965
she fell in love
with this family,

17
00:00:39,034 --> 00:00:40,482
widowed dad, bill,

18
00:00:40,551 --> 00:00:42,724
and his children,
Kyle and Brittany.

19
00:00:42,793 --> 00:00:46,724
Thus, Kristin sacrificed
her own immortality

20
00:00:46,793 --> 00:00:48,862
and all memory of who she was

21
00:00:48,931 --> 00:00:50,482
to save Christmas

22
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:53,586
and foil
rudolfa's sinister plan,

23
00:00:53,655 --> 00:00:55,793
but that was last year,

24
00:00:55,862 --> 00:01:00,172
and this
istwice upon a Christmas.

25
00:01:00,241 --> 00:01:02,413
[ ♪♪ ]

26
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:22,586
As usual...Incredible.

27
00:02:22,655 --> 00:02:24,103
Control yourself.

28
00:02:24,172 --> 00:02:25,344
I remember

29
00:02:25,413 --> 00:02:27,172
when you taught Kristin
to do that.

30
00:02:27,241 --> 00:02:30,137
It seems such a long time ago
since we last saw her.

31
00:02:30,206 --> 00:02:31,793
Yes,

32
00:02:31,862 --> 00:02:33,827
but she's very happy
where she is.

33
00:02:33,896 --> 00:02:35,344
Yes, I suppose she is.

34
00:02:35,413 --> 00:02:37,000
That's very true.

35
00:02:38,724 --> 00:02:40,172
[ Deejay ]:
Happy holidays, willowbrook.

36
00:02:40,241 --> 00:02:42,448
It's christmastime in Oregon
again,

37
00:02:42,517 --> 00:02:44,275
42 degrees downtown.

38
00:02:44,344 --> 00:02:47,517
Here's another song to put you
in that Christmas spirit.

39
00:02:47,586 --> 00:02:49,103
[ ♪♪ ]

40
00:02:53,758 --> 00:02:56,000
Can I please have the tape?

41
00:02:56,068 --> 00:02:59,000
Okay,
now, hold still, Kyle.

42
00:03:06,862 --> 00:03:09,275
Thank you, Brittany.

43
00:03:09,344 --> 00:03:11,172
I just want to make sure
Brittany's next.

44
00:03:11,241 --> 00:03:13,344
Oh, definitely, Kyle.

45
00:03:13,413 --> 00:03:14,620
That's how the game works.

46
00:03:14,689 --> 00:03:16,034
We wrap up you,

47
00:03:16,103 --> 00:03:18,310
and then you get to wrap up
someone else.

48
00:03:18,379 --> 00:03:19,931
I saw that.

49
00:03:30,413 --> 00:03:32,413
[ Telephone ringing ]

50
00:03:32,482 --> 00:03:34,000
Truce, truce, truce.

51
00:03:37,068 --> 00:03:38,793
Hello?

52
00:03:38,862 --> 00:03:40,827
Hey, brit. It's daddy.

53
00:03:40,896 --> 00:03:42,344
Hi, daddy.

54
00:03:42,413 --> 00:03:43,827
Ask him when he thinks
he'll be home.

55
00:03:43,896 --> 00:03:45,551
When will you be home?

56
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:50,103
I've got two more meetings,
so...I guess about 7:00.

57
00:03:50,172 --> 00:03:53,655
Honey, can Kristin
hear you?

58
00:03:53,724 --> 00:03:55,517
No.

59
00:03:55,586 --> 00:03:58,206
Okay.
Do you think she knows anything?

60
00:03:58,275 --> 00:03:59,965
I don't think so.

61
00:04:00,034 --> 00:04:01,862
And Kyle hasn't said anything,
right?

62
00:04:01,931 --> 00:04:04,758
For a change, no.

63
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:07,103
You know what? I have to go.

64
00:04:07,172 --> 00:04:09,448
See you later. Bye.

65
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,379
What was that
all about?

66
00:04:14,448 --> 00:04:15,724
Nothing.

67
00:04:15,793 --> 00:04:17,172
You know, Kristin,

68
00:04:17,241 --> 00:04:19,068
it's not that easy
to surprise dad.

69
00:04:19,137 --> 00:04:20,724
Believe me. I've tried.

70
00:04:20,793 --> 00:04:23,172
You know,
he's been so busy with work.

71
00:04:23,241 --> 00:04:25,793
I bet he's probably
forgotten all about it.

72
00:04:25,862 --> 00:04:27,103
Rachel's dad
doesn't celebrate birthdays

73
00:04:27,172 --> 00:04:28,931
anymore.

74
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,172
His last birthday cake
had so many candles on it,

75
00:04:31,241 --> 00:04:32,931
it set off
the smoke alarms.

76
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,448
You should always
celebrate your birthday.

77
00:04:35,517 --> 00:04:36,931
It's such
an important day.

78
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,586
It reminds US of the miracle
each one of US is,

79
00:04:39,655 --> 00:04:41,413
all the special
things

80
00:04:41,482 --> 00:04:43,241
that come together and make you,
you.

81
00:04:43,310 --> 00:04:45,034
It has nothing to do

82
00:04:45,103 --> 00:04:46,517
with how old you are.

83
00:04:46,586 --> 00:04:48,689
It's about how wonderful
life is.

84
00:04:48,758 --> 00:04:50,379
Maybe you should talk
to Rachel's dad.

85
00:04:50,448 --> 00:04:52,620
Man, what happened
in here?

86
00:04:54,931 --> 00:04:56,172
Small paper fight,
uncle Johnny.

87
00:04:56,241 --> 00:04:57,586
Why didn't you call me?

88
00:04:59,896 --> 00:05:01,275
Ow.

89
00:05:01,344 --> 00:05:02,724
Hey, no paper fights
without me.

90
00:05:02,793 --> 00:05:04,344
Paper cut!

91
00:05:20,206 --> 00:05:21,965
What are you looking at?

92
00:05:30,965 --> 00:05:33,965
I hate this!

93
00:05:34,034 --> 00:05:35,482
And you,

94
00:05:35,551 --> 00:05:37,482
you had better give Santa
a good report

95
00:05:37,551 --> 00:05:39,275
on the job I've been doing.

96
00:05:39,344 --> 00:05:41,965
Santa...

97
00:05:42,034 --> 00:05:45,000
That old man
is going to kill me.

98
00:05:52,379 --> 00:05:54,000
Look at me.

99
00:05:54,068 --> 00:05:56,275
I'm a wreck.

100
00:05:56,344 --> 00:05:58,413
First, I have to Polish
all the ribbon

101
00:05:58,482 --> 00:06:00,172
on the presents,

102
00:06:00,241 --> 00:06:03,034
and then I have to clean up
after all of those birds.

103
00:06:03,103 --> 00:06:04,689
Seven swans a-swimming,

104
00:06:04,758 --> 00:06:05,689
six geese a-laying,

105
00:06:05,758 --> 00:06:07,172
four calling birds,

106
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:09,103
three French hens,

107
00:06:09,172 --> 00:06:11,724
two stinking turtle doves,

108
00:06:11,793 --> 00:06:14,482
and that partridge
in that rotten pear tree.

109
00:06:14,551 --> 00:06:18,275
It's too much...

110
00:06:19,586 --> 00:06:21,344
It's dad.

111
00:06:21,413 --> 00:06:23,172
It's dad. Shh.

112
00:06:23,241 --> 00:06:25,034
I'm here.
Here I am, dad.

113
00:06:25,103 --> 00:06:28,034
I...whoo, I'm working away,
just like you told me to.

114
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:34,862
Yes, I can see.

115
00:06:34,931 --> 00:06:38,896
Whew.
Almost done, don't you think?

116
00:06:38,965 --> 00:06:42,310
I hope you've learned something
from doing all these chores.

117
00:06:42,379 --> 00:06:43,862
Oh, I have.

118
00:06:43,931 --> 00:06:46,068
I really, really have.

119
00:06:46,137 --> 00:06:47,448
And what is it
that you've learned,

120
00:06:47,517 --> 00:06:49,413
rudolfa?

121
00:06:49,482 --> 00:06:52,931
Well, I've learned
that ribbon is only shiny

122
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,103
if you buff it...A lot.

123
00:06:55,172 --> 00:06:56,689
Yes. What else?

124
00:06:56,758 --> 00:07:00,620
Those birds eat way too much.

125
00:07:00,689 --> 00:07:02,379
Have you learned your lesson,
rudolfa?

126
00:07:02,448 --> 00:07:03,724
Lesson?

127
00:07:03,793 --> 00:07:05,241
Yeah, don't get caught.

128
00:07:05,310 --> 00:07:06,344
That's the lesson.

129
00:07:06,413 --> 00:07:08,586
I'm sorry. What was that?

130
00:07:08,655 --> 00:07:09,862
Oh, yes, I did.

131
00:07:09,931 --> 00:07:11,310
I learned a lesson.

132
00:07:11,379 --> 00:07:13,862
Definitely.

133
00:07:13,931 --> 00:07:16,413
Are you sorry
for what you did

134
00:07:16,482 --> 00:07:17,793
last year?

135
00:07:17,862 --> 00:07:22,586
I'm very, very, very sorry.

136
00:07:22,655 --> 00:07:24,137
Very well, then.

137
00:07:24,206 --> 00:07:26,517
I release you
from all further chores.

138
00:07:26,586 --> 00:07:28,758
Oh, thank you, thank you,
thank you, daddy.

139
00:07:28,827 --> 00:07:29,793
Oh, thank you,

140
00:07:29,862 --> 00:07:31,724
and I'll be good.

141
00:07:31,793 --> 00:07:33,241
I really will, dad.

142
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,896
Well, you're going
to have to be.

143
00:07:34,965 --> 00:07:36,827
I'm going to need
your help this year

144
00:07:36,896 --> 00:07:37,965
with Kristin gone.

145
00:07:38,034 --> 00:07:39,206
I'm here.

146
00:07:39,275 --> 00:07:40,344
I'm the one

147
00:07:40,413 --> 00:07:41,551
that stayed loyal
to the pole,

148
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:43,000
and to you.

149
00:07:43,068 --> 00:07:44,655
No, no, no,
I didn't go anywhere.

150
00:07:44,724 --> 00:07:46,896
I was happy
just being here

151
00:07:46,965 --> 00:07:48,379
with you and mother.

152
00:07:48,448 --> 00:07:49,931
Yes, it's true.

153
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,689
You did stay here.

154
00:07:51,758 --> 00:07:53,000
You stayed here,

155
00:07:53,068 --> 00:07:54,896
even though you wanted
to turn Christmas day

156
00:07:54,965 --> 00:07:56,655
into Christmas fools' day!

157
00:07:56,724 --> 00:07:58,206
Well, yeah,

158
00:07:58,275 --> 00:08:00,517
but that's all behind US now,
right?

159
00:08:00,586 --> 00:08:04,275
Well, it's going
to have to be.

160
00:08:04,344 --> 00:08:06,344
You're going to have to
do some of the duties

161
00:08:06,413 --> 00:08:07,724
that were Kristin's.

162
00:08:07,793 --> 00:08:08,793
Well, of course.

163
00:08:08,862 --> 00:08:09,793
I'll have to
take her place

164
00:08:09,862 --> 00:08:10,793
in some things.

165
00:08:10,862 --> 00:08:12,172
I'll be happy to.

166
00:08:12,241 --> 00:08:14,482
Filling Kristin's shoes
is a difficult task.

167
00:08:14,551 --> 00:08:16,689
That's because she's got
such big feet.

168
00:08:16,758 --> 00:08:18,034
I'm sorry.
What was that?

169
00:08:18,103 --> 00:08:19,793
Oh, I said, um...

170
00:08:19,862 --> 00:08:22,000
It's a challenge
I hope I can meet.

171
00:08:22,068 --> 00:08:24,379
Well, you have no choice.

172
00:08:24,448 --> 00:08:25,965
We're behind again
this year.

173
00:08:26,034 --> 00:08:28,896
I just can't seem
to get organized.

174
00:08:28,965 --> 00:08:30,758
Well, we're beginning
right away,

175
00:08:30,827 --> 00:08:33,241
so get yourself ready.

176
00:08:33,310 --> 00:08:34,758
Oh, don't worry.

177
00:08:34,827 --> 00:08:37,068
I'll be ready.

178
00:08:37,137 --> 00:08:42,275
You can bet I'll be ready.

179
00:08:42,344 --> 00:08:43,517
Guys...

180
00:08:43,586 --> 00:08:45,620
♪ We wish you
a happy birthday ♪

181
00:08:45,689 --> 00:08:47,827
♪ we wish you
a happy birthday ♪

182
00:08:47,896 --> 00:08:53,862
♪ we wish you a happy birthday
and many more years ♪♪

183
00:08:53,931 --> 00:08:56,310
Well, that's a new one.

184
00:08:56,379 --> 00:08:58,137
Come on, dad.
Blow out the candles.

185
00:08:58,206 --> 00:08:59,827
Okay.

186
00:09:05,172 --> 00:09:06,482
Whoo!

187
00:09:06,551 --> 00:09:07,965
Whoo!

188
00:09:09,379 --> 00:09:11,862
I'll go get the presents.

189
00:09:11,931 --> 00:09:13,620
This looks fantastic, Kristin.

190
00:09:13,689 --> 00:09:16,206
I'll say. Where's
everyone else's piece?

191
00:09:16,275 --> 00:09:18,172
Here you go.

192
00:09:18,241 --> 00:09:19,689
Whoa.

193
00:09:19,758 --> 00:09:22,206
Okay, open them.

194
00:09:22,275 --> 00:09:23,586
Okay.

195
00:09:23,655 --> 00:09:26,310
Do I see a gift here
from Kristin?

196
00:09:26,379 --> 00:09:28,482
Mine is the one
with the green bow.

197
00:09:28,551 --> 00:09:33,344
You know, I'm sure
it's a wonderful present,

198
00:09:33,413 --> 00:09:36,310
but it's not the one
I'm looking for.

199
00:09:39,689 --> 00:09:42,586
Scoot your chair back a little
from the table.

200
00:09:44,724 --> 00:09:46,586
Okay.

201
00:09:46,655 --> 00:09:48,241
Like this?

202
00:09:50,344 --> 00:09:52,620
A little more, I think.

203
00:09:55,586 --> 00:09:58,137
Okay.

204
00:09:58,206 --> 00:09:59,689
Great.

205
00:10:01,482 --> 00:10:02,379
Are you okay, bill?

206
00:10:02,448 --> 00:10:04,275
Oh, yeah, yeah.

207
00:10:04,344 --> 00:10:08,310
Now, the gift
that I'm looking for from you

208
00:10:08,379 --> 00:10:12,551
is...is really just one word,

209
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:14,413
just "yes."

210
00:10:21,275 --> 00:10:23,517
I'm asking you to marry me,

211
00:10:23,586 --> 00:10:25,586
and by "me," I mean "we,"

212
00:10:25,655 --> 00:10:27,413
obviously.

213
00:10:30,344 --> 00:10:32,275
Oh, bill.

214
00:10:35,103 --> 00:10:37,448
It's beautiful.

215
00:10:37,517 --> 00:10:39,310
Did you two know about this?

216
00:10:39,379 --> 00:10:41,103
I helped pick out the ring.

217
00:10:44,793 --> 00:10:46,413
It's wonderful...

218
00:10:50,724 --> 00:10:52,448
And you two...

219
00:10:52,517 --> 00:10:55,931
Oh, I love you so much.

220
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,448
I love you, bill.

221
00:10:57,517 --> 00:10:59,758
Am I going to get the gift
that I'm looking for?

222
00:10:59,827 --> 00:11:03,413
I'm sorry, bill.

223
00:11:03,482 --> 00:11:08,482
No, I...I can't.

224
00:11:14,034 --> 00:11:16,827
Excuse me.

225
00:11:16,896 --> 00:11:19,000
Well, who wants cake, huh?

226
00:11:29,448 --> 00:11:31,724
You don't want
to be our mom?

227
00:11:33,586 --> 00:11:35,172
Of course I do,
sweetheart.

228
00:11:35,241 --> 00:11:37,344
I don't want anything
else in the world.

229
00:11:37,413 --> 00:11:39,172
Then tell me why,
Kristin,

230
00:11:39,241 --> 00:11:40,655
because
I don't understand.

231
00:11:40,724 --> 00:11:42,206
It's me.

232
00:11:42,275 --> 00:11:43,517
Don't you know

233
00:11:43,586 --> 00:11:45,862
how much I've wanted
this moment?

234
00:11:45,931 --> 00:11:49,137
How can I be your wife
and be here for the kids

235
00:11:49,206 --> 00:11:51,586
if I don't know who I am?

236
00:11:51,655 --> 00:11:52,724
Okay, so maybe

237
00:11:52,793 --> 00:11:54,241
I'll try to call
the nanny agency again

238
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:55,379
and see
what happens.

239
00:11:55,448 --> 00:11:56,689
I've called them again,

240
00:11:56,758 --> 00:11:58,034
and they still have no record

241
00:11:58,103 --> 00:11:59,896
of me
ever being registered there,

242
00:11:59,965 --> 00:12:02,517
and I don't know
who else to call.

243
00:12:02,586 --> 00:12:04,517
I have no information
to start with,

244
00:12:04,586 --> 00:12:08,103
no hometown, no anything.

245
00:12:08,172 --> 00:12:12,068
We know everything
we need to know about you now.

246
00:12:12,137 --> 00:12:15,689
You are a warm, wonderful,
loving woman

247
00:12:15,758 --> 00:12:16,758
who I love,

248
00:12:16,827 --> 00:12:18,206
who we love,

249
00:12:18,275 --> 00:12:20,275
and who we need,
Kristin,

250
00:12:20,344 --> 00:12:21,931
and want in our lives
forever,

251
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,862
and, you know,
you don't have a memory

252
00:12:23,931 --> 00:12:26,310
of who you were
when you came in our front door,

253
00:12:26,379 --> 00:12:27,862
and I don't care,

254
00:12:27,931 --> 00:12:30,379
and whatever you were
before then,

255
00:12:30,448 --> 00:12:32,241
it just doesn't make
a difference

256
00:12:32,310 --> 00:12:35,448
to me or the kids.

257
00:12:35,517 --> 00:12:36,931
Yeah, we don't care
who you are.

258
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,172
He means

259
00:12:38,241 --> 00:12:39,000
that we know you
and love you

260
00:12:39,068 --> 00:12:39,965
already.

261
00:12:40,034 --> 00:12:44,862
But it makes a difference to me.

262
00:12:44,931 --> 00:12:48,034
I mean, tonight,
you had a birthday,

263
00:12:48,103 --> 00:12:50,379
and, Kyle, you have one,

264
00:12:50,448 --> 00:12:52,379
August 24th,

265
00:12:52,448 --> 00:12:54,758
and Brittany,
march 11th.

266
00:12:54,827 --> 00:12:58,758
Can you tell me
when my birthday is?

267
00:13:00,275 --> 00:13:02,344
I don't even know
how to drive a car.

268
00:13:02,413 --> 00:13:04,551
I mean,
how is that possible?

269
00:13:04,620 --> 00:13:05,655
Where did I live

270
00:13:05,724 --> 00:13:07,586
that I never learned
how to drive?

271
00:13:07,655 --> 00:13:09,241
Hey, I'll be learning
in a couple of years.

272
00:13:09,310 --> 00:13:10,586
I'll drive you around.

273
00:13:10,655 --> 00:13:12,275
Everything here is so wonderful,

274
00:13:12,344 --> 00:13:13,793
but, lately,

275
00:13:13,862 --> 00:13:15,310
finding out

276
00:13:15,379 --> 00:13:18,068
has seemed
more and more important.

277
00:13:18,137 --> 00:13:20,000
I mean, face it.

278
00:13:20,068 --> 00:13:21,793
Have you ever met
anyone like me,

279
00:13:21,862 --> 00:13:24,448
someone who knows nothing
about her past?

280
00:13:24,517 --> 00:13:26,034
Let's just
make a deal.

281
00:13:26,103 --> 00:13:26,793
A deal?

282
00:13:26,862 --> 00:13:27,655
A deal.

283
00:13:27,724 --> 00:13:30,172
You give me
my "yes,"

284
00:13:30,241 --> 00:13:32,034
and I promise you

285
00:13:32,103 --> 00:13:35,310
