01:05:35,241 --> 01:05:38,517
Snow.

1346
01:05:47,413 --> 01:05:49,724
"From daddy to Kristin,

1347
01:05:49,793 --> 01:05:53,034
"those who believe

1348
01:05:53,103 --> 01:05:55,896
are always
rewarded with the truth."

1349
01:06:15,724 --> 01:06:16,896
This is
the north pole?

1350
01:06:16,965 --> 01:06:17,896
Forget merry.

1351
01:06:17,965 --> 01:06:19,344
This is
scary Christmas.

1352
01:06:19,413 --> 01:06:22,068
Where's dad?

1353
01:06:22,137 --> 01:06:23,448
Maybe my power

1354
01:06:23,517 --> 01:06:25,620
wasn't strong enough
to get US all here.

1355
01:06:25,689 --> 01:06:29,000
Well, I'm going
to remember everything

1356
01:06:29,068 --> 01:06:30,172
so I can tell him
about it

1357
01:06:30,241 --> 01:06:31,724
when we get back.

1358
01:06:31,793 --> 01:06:33,655
Me too,

1359
01:06:33,724 --> 01:06:35,448
although I may leave
this part out.

1360
01:06:35,517 --> 01:06:38,137
Yeah.
It's worse than I thought.

1361
01:06:38,206 --> 01:06:39,206
Dad?

1362
01:06:39,275 --> 01:06:41,103
Mom?

1363
01:06:41,172 --> 01:06:43,586
Come with me.

1364
01:06:50,034 --> 01:06:52,310
Dad!

1365
01:06:52,379 --> 01:06:53,551
No, no it couldn't be.

1366
01:06:53,620 --> 01:06:55,448
Dad, it's me.
It's Kristin.

1367
01:06:55,517 --> 01:06:56,379
Kristin.

1368
01:06:56,448 --> 01:06:57,482
Are you back?

1369
01:06:57,551 --> 01:06:58,586
Have you come back?

1370
01:06:58,655 --> 01:06:59,620
Yes, dad. I'm here.

1371
01:06:59,689 --> 01:07:01,551
What can I do?

1372
01:07:01,620 --> 01:07:04,034
There's nothing
that can be done.

1373
01:07:04,103 --> 01:07:05,655
But where's mother?

1374
01:07:05,724 --> 01:07:07,413
She's packing what little
they've left US.

1375
01:07:07,482 --> 01:07:09,241
We're leaving.

1376
01:07:09,310 --> 01:07:11,310
Everyone else
has already gone...

1377
01:07:11,379 --> 01:07:15,206
I guess I knew this
would happen one day.

1378
01:07:15,275 --> 01:07:17,965
The new Santa is
out there right now,

1379
01:07:18,034 --> 01:07:21,275
getting the gifts ready,

1380
01:07:21,344 --> 01:07:22,517
making people happy,

1381
01:07:22,586 --> 01:07:23,413
just like I used to do.

1382
01:07:23,482 --> 01:07:25,034
What new Santa?

1383
01:07:25,103 --> 01:07:28,206
When they don't want you,
it's cruel,

1384
01:07:28,275 --> 01:07:30,517
even for Santa,

1385
01:07:30,586 --> 01:07:32,655
but I had a long run,

1386
01:07:32,724 --> 01:07:34,517
but you lose a step...

1387
01:07:34,586 --> 01:07:36,931
And they push you
down the stairs.

1388
01:07:37,000 --> 01:07:39,413
Dad, that's not true.

1389
01:07:39,482 --> 01:07:41,448
Is that what you think
is going on?

1390
01:07:41,517 --> 01:07:43,965
It isn't.

1391
01:07:44,034 --> 01:07:44,965
Dad, it's...

1392
01:07:45,034 --> 01:07:46,206
It's rudolfa...

1393
01:07:46,275 --> 01:07:48,034
I know she's done

1394
01:07:48,103 --> 01:07:50,206
her fair share of mischief
in the past.

1395
01:07:50,275 --> 01:07:51,931
But, no, this time, it's me.

1396
01:07:52,000 --> 01:07:53,896
I've done something
to deserve this,

1397
01:07:53,965 --> 01:07:57,862
but i--
I don't know what it is.

1398
01:07:57,931 --> 01:08:01,344
Ooh!

1399
01:08:03,448 --> 01:08:04,655
Dad, I'd like you to meet--

1400
01:08:04,724 --> 01:08:06,310
Kyle and Brittany.

1401
01:08:06,379 --> 01:08:10,206
Beautiful children.

1402
01:08:10,275 --> 01:08:11,827
Oh, dear.

1403
01:08:11,896 --> 01:08:13,896
I don't have
the littlest thing

1404
01:08:13,965 --> 01:08:15,758
to give them
for Christmas.

1405
01:08:15,827 --> 01:08:17,000
It's so embarrassing.

1406
01:08:17,068 --> 01:08:18,655
Dad, now, don't you worry.

1407
01:08:18,724 --> 01:08:20,206
It's not even
Christmas Eve yet.

1408
01:08:20,275 --> 01:08:23,448
I want you to do
what you always taught me--

1409
01:08:23,517 --> 01:08:24,482
have hope.

1410
01:08:24,551 --> 01:08:26,000
Have faith.

1411
01:08:26,068 --> 01:08:29,103
"Those who believe
are rewarded with the truth."

1412
01:08:29,172 --> 01:08:30,344
What you're saying is

1413
01:08:30,413 --> 01:08:32,310
that even I
don't believe in Santa

1414
01:08:32,379 --> 01:08:35,379
if this is my reward.

1415
01:08:35,448 --> 01:08:37,827
Dad, you are Santa claus.

1416
01:08:37,896 --> 01:08:40,103
Don't ever forget who you are.

1417
01:08:40,172 --> 01:08:41,413
And it isn't because

1418
01:08:41,482 --> 01:08:44,172
you have a white beard
and wear a red suit.

1419
01:08:44,241 --> 01:08:46,379
It's because in your eyes

1420
01:08:46,448 --> 01:08:48,862
are the hopes
of millions of children.

1421
01:08:48,931 --> 01:08:50,103
On your shoulders

1422
01:08:50,172 --> 01:08:52,000
is the weight
of millions of dreams

1423
01:08:52,068 --> 01:08:53,344
waiting to be delivered.

1424
01:08:53,413 --> 01:08:58,137
You are so important
to the world, dad,

1425
01:08:58,206 --> 01:09:00,137
not only because you give,

1426
01:09:00,206 --> 01:09:04,068
but because you show others
what it is to give.

1427
01:09:04,137 --> 01:09:07,758
That's who Santa claus is
and that's who you are,

1428
01:09:07,827 --> 01:09:12,827
and that's why we have to get
the north pole back for you.

1429
01:09:12,896 --> 01:09:17,034
Oh, Kristin.

1430
01:09:17,103 --> 01:09:18,068
Don't worry, dad.

1431
01:09:18,137 --> 01:09:19,758
I'll take care of it.

1432
01:09:19,827 --> 01:09:23,517
I'm so glad we've been able
to come to an agreement, Donald,

1433
01:09:23,586 --> 01:09:26,344
finally.

1434
01:09:26,413 --> 01:09:27,965
I've got to go.

1435
01:09:28,034 --> 01:09:29,965
Kristin!

1436
01:09:30,034 --> 01:09:32,310
How surprising
to see you.

1437
01:09:32,379 --> 01:09:35,103
New year. Same you.

1438
01:09:35,172 --> 01:09:38,896
Have you taken up haiku
since you abandoned US?

1439
01:09:38,965 --> 01:09:41,517
You won't
get away with this.

1440
01:09:41,586 --> 01:09:43,517
That old song.

1441
01:09:43,586 --> 01:09:45,068
Take a look around,
Kristin.

1442
01:09:45,137 --> 01:09:46,551
I've already gotten
away with it.

1443
01:09:46,620 --> 01:09:48,482
Did you notice?

1444
01:09:48,551 --> 01:09:52,241
There's almost nothing left
of your precious pole.

1445
01:09:52,310 --> 01:09:54,655
I saw it.

1446
01:09:54,724 --> 01:09:55,551
So perfect.

1447
01:09:55,620 --> 01:09:57,068
Everybody wanted

1448
01:09:57,137 --> 01:09:59,034
his or her own
piece of the pole.

1449
01:09:59,103 --> 01:10:00,896
"Believe this, believe that."

1450
01:10:00,965 --> 01:10:03,068
It's all talk, really.

1451
01:10:03,137 --> 01:10:04,620
What they care about

1452
01:10:04,689 --> 01:10:06,551
is having something
they can hold in their hands.

1453
01:10:06,620 --> 01:10:07,827
Right, kids?

1454
01:10:07,896 --> 01:10:10,275
Makes you feel good?

1455
01:10:10,344 --> 01:10:12,827
Then brick by brick, bye-bye.

1456
01:10:12,896 --> 01:10:13,724
We just thought

1457
01:10:13,793 --> 01:10:15,068
it would be
a nice gift.

1458
01:10:15,137 --> 01:10:18,448
Santa claus isn't going anywhere
this year.

1459
01:10:18,517 --> 01:10:20,586
The sleigh
is in a hundred pieces

1460
01:10:20,655 --> 01:10:22,965
spread out
in the grubby little hands

1461
01:10:23,034 --> 01:10:24,068
of half a dozen countries.

1462
01:10:24,137 --> 01:10:25,620
And the reindeer?

1463
01:10:25,689 --> 01:10:28,551
I sold them
to a collector in Ohio.

1464
01:10:28,620 --> 01:10:29,931
Bought the whole set.

1465
01:10:30,000 --> 01:10:31,586
The reindeer are gone?

1466
01:10:31,655 --> 01:10:33,172
Filthy animals.

1467
01:10:33,241 --> 01:10:34,931
I say "good riddance."

1468
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:37,482
It's all been sold.

1469
01:10:37,551 --> 01:10:38,862
Why not?

1470
01:10:38,931 --> 01:10:40,103
People greedy
for Christmas

1471
01:10:40,172 --> 01:10:41,724
bought it all,

1472
01:10:41,793 --> 01:10:46,172
and while they were buying it,
they destroyed it.

1473
01:10:46,241 --> 01:10:47,758
So now...

1474
01:10:47,827 --> 01:10:51,655
Rudolfa and Donald's
hotel and casino is going up.

1475
01:10:53,655 --> 01:10:56,000
We're paving paradise
and putting up a parking lot--

1476
01:10:56,068 --> 01:10:57,862
several, in fact.

1477
01:10:57,931 --> 01:10:59,689
My guess is

1478
01:10:59,758 --> 01:11:02,620
the same people that bought
the pieces of the pole

1479
01:11:02,689 --> 01:11:04,655
will be the ones
that will make the trek here

1480
01:11:04,724 --> 01:11:07,551
to stay at the hotel.

1481
01:11:07,620 --> 01:11:09,034
By the way, do you know
who owns the south pole?

1482
01:11:09,103 --> 01:11:11,206
Because
at this point in my career,

1483
01:11:11,275 --> 01:11:12,344
I don't know,

1484
01:11:12,413 --> 01:11:16,724
I feel the need
to go...Really global.

1485
01:11:16,793 --> 01:11:18,379
Well, I can find out.

1486
01:11:18,448 --> 01:11:20,137
Because when
you're hot in this business,

1487
01:11:20,206 --> 01:11:21,655
you have to keep on the move.

1488
01:11:21,724 --> 01:11:24,965
They've got
all those penguins up there.

1489
01:11:25,034 --> 01:11:27,000
I can probably
sell those off like chickens.

1490
01:11:27,068 --> 01:11:29,965
Once the birds are gone,
the building begins.

1491
01:11:33,379 --> 01:11:34,931
Wow. That was
your sister?

1492
01:11:35,000 --> 01:11:35,896
Good ol' sis.

1493
01:11:35,965 --> 01:11:38,310
Poor Christmas.

1494
01:11:47,724 --> 01:11:49,758
♪ God rest
ye merry presents ♪

1495
01:11:49,827 --> 01:11:51,482
♪ under the tree you go ♪

1496
01:11:51,551 --> 01:11:53,241
♪ tonight Kristin
is making food ♪

1497
01:11:53,310 --> 01:11:55,103
♪ into my mouth it'll go ♪

1498
01:11:55,172 --> 01:11:56,758
♪ we'll eat and eat
and eat some more ♪

1499
01:11:56,827 --> 01:11:58,793
♪ and then we'll eat some more ♪

1500
01:12:04,172 --> 01:12:05,793
Hey, bill.

1501
01:12:05,862 --> 01:12:07,034
What's going on?

1502
01:12:07,103 --> 01:12:08,137
Where are the Kristin
and the kids?

1503
01:12:10,241 --> 01:12:11,551
Gone.

1504
01:12:11,620 --> 01:12:16,310
"Gone" as in shopping?
Or gone as in..."Gone"?

1505
01:12:16,379 --> 01:12:20,931
Gone as in...

1506
01:12:21,000 --> 01:12:22,517
You know what?

1507
01:12:22,586 --> 01:12:24,379
I'm not even sure
that "gone" really covers it.

1508
01:12:24,448 --> 01:12:26,172
Boy, that's bad.

1509
01:12:26,241 --> 01:12:28,172
"Gone" covers a lot.

1510
01:12:28,241 --> 01:12:29,379
I don't know
how this could be...

1511
01:12:29,448 --> 01:12:30,689
But I don't have

1512
01:12:30,758 --> 01:12:32,689
another explanation
for it.

1513
01:12:32,758 --> 01:12:34,344
Do you mind if I sit?

1514
01:12:34,413 --> 01:12:36,551
I have a feeling
this could take a while.

1515
01:12:39,517 --> 01:12:42,241
What are we
going to do, Kristin?

1516
01:12:54,413 --> 01:12:56,379
♪ So order now
it's time to buy ♪

1517
01:12:56,448 --> 01:12:58,724
♪ we are carrying
a big supply ♪

1518
01:12:58,793 --> 01:13:00,586
♪ don't delay
they won't last... ♪

1519
01:13:02,655 --> 01:13:04,310
Follow me.

1520
01:13:08,896 --> 01:13:13,172
♪ Each guaranteed and certified
no lies, no fakes, no tricks ♪

1521
01:13:13,241 --> 01:13:15,793
♪ pay what you can
don't think twice ♪

1522
01:13:15,862 --> 01:13:18,413
♪ we don't care
about the price ♪

1523
01:13:18,482 --> 01:13:21,482
♪ isn't that nice? ♪

1524
01:13:21,551 --> 01:13:24,724
♪ Buy a piece of the pole ♪

1525
01:13:24,793 --> 01:13:37,000
♪ now you can own
your own piece of the pole... ♪

1526
01:13:37,068 --> 01:13:39,551
Hey, this is the stuff
from the commercial.

1527
01:13:39,620 --> 01:13:41,896
We're going to broadcast
one last time.

1528
01:13:41,965 --> 01:13:44,724
Standby for transmission.

1529
01:13:48,068 --> 01:13:52,724
There is one thing
we might be able to do.

1530
01:13:54,241 --> 01:13:55,586
Oh, wahoo?

1531
01:13:57,724 --> 01:13:59,172
Kristin?

1532
01:14:14,310 --> 01:14:16,310
We have to figure
this thing out,

1533
01:14:16,379 --> 01:14:17,310
and fast.

1534
01:14:17,379 --> 01:14:18,310
That's right.

1535
01:14:18,379 --> 01:14:19,827
For a limited time,

1536
01:14:19,896 --> 01:14:23,827
you too
can own a piece of the pole.

1537
01:14:23,896 --> 01:14:25,241
I love her.

1538
01:14:25,310 --> 01:14:27,517
I know that.

1539
01:14:27,586 --> 01:14:31,172
And I was here when they...

1540
01:14:31,241 --> 01:14:32,517
When they disappeared in that...

1541
01:14:32,586 --> 01:14:34,827
That swirl of snow.

1542
01:14:34,896 --> 01:14:36,275
I saw that.

1543
01:14:36,344 --> 01:14:39,827
So...that must be...

1544
01:14:39,896 --> 01:14:41,344
Some kind of proof

1545
01:14:41,413 --> 01:14:46,034
that Kristin is...

1546
01:14:46,103 --> 01:14:48,000
That Kristin
is Santa's daughter.

1547
01:14:48,068 --> 01:14:51,172
What?

1548
01:14:51,241 --> 01:14:53,344
That's the only thing
that makes sense.

1549
01:14:53,413 --> 01:14:55,862
That makes sense
and cloning doesn't?

1550
01:14:55,931 --> 01:14:57,620
Johnny, she comes
out of nowhere, right?

1551
01:14:57,689 --> 01:14:59,344
She shows up here

1552
01:14:59,413 --> 01:15:03,068
with a big red velvet bag
for her luggage.

1553
01:15:03,137 --> 01:15:05,586
She's an expert
on Christmas.

1554
01:15:05,655 --> 01:15:07,448
Her favorite colors
are red and green.

1555
01:15:07,517 --> 01:15:11,655
I mean, her favorite song
is "silent night".

1556
01:15:11,724 --> 01:15:14,241
She's the most loving,
the most forgiving person

1557
01:15:14,310 --> 01:15:16,620
I've ever met...

1558
01:15:16,689 --> 01:15:19,965
And her name is Kristin claus.

1559
01:15:24,103 --> 01:15:25,724
You lucky...

1560
01:15:25,793 --> 01:15:27,206
And you know what?

1561
01:15:27,275 --> 01:15:28,827
Now that I know it,

1562
01:15:28,896 --> 01:15:29,689
I know I've known it
all along.

1563
01:15:29,758 --> 01:15:31,413
I just--

1564
01:15:31,482 --> 01:15:33,000
I was afraid
to admit it.

1565
01:15:33,068 --> 01:15:34,862
You're losing me.

1566
01:15:34,931 --> 01:15:36,413
Well, I love her.

1567
01:15:36,482 --> 01:15:38,000
But to be married
to Santa's daughter?

1568
01:15:38,068 --> 01:15:39,310
That's a little strange,
don't you think?

1569
01:15:39,379 --> 01:15:44,620
Yeah, that is strange...

1570
01:15:44,689 --> 01:15:47,896
Think of the story
in the tabloids.

1571
01:15:47,965 --> 01:15:51,103
Johnny, if you want
to spend another minute

1572
01:15:51,172 --> 01:15:52,551
under this roof,

1573
01:15:52,620 --> 01:15:55,758
don't even
think that again.

1574
01:15:58,034 --> 01:15:59,344
Oh, my god, you're right.

1575
01:15:59,413 --> 01:16:01,689
If we get married,

1576
01:16:01,758 --> 01:16:02,931
then Kristin

1577
01:16:03,000 --> 01:16:04,034
could never even
breathe a word

1578
01:16:04,103 --> 01:16:07,517
of who she really is...

1579
01:16:07,586 --> 01:16:09,413
Please stand by what?

1580
01:16:09,482 --> 01:16:11,206
The thing is

1581
01:16:11,275 --> 01:16:12,517
that the north pole

1582
01:16:12,586 --> 01:16:14,517
doesn't belong
to any one person.

1583
01:16:14,586 --> 01:16:16,448
It can't,

1584
01:16:16,517 --> 01:16:18,206
because it already belongs
to everyone--

1585
01:16:18,275 --> 01:16:20,793
to everyone who believes,

1586
01:16:20,862 --> 01:16:22,413
and it can only exist

1587
01:16:22,482 --> 01:16:25,413
if everyone believes
in the whole thing together.

1588
01:16:25,482 --> 01:16:28,931
That's what makes
the north pole powerful.

1589
01:16:29,000 --> 01:16:31,310
That's what makes it important.

1590
01:16:31,379 --> 01:16:35,482
It's everyone believing
together.

1591
01:16:35,551 --> 01:16:37,827
But now with people having

1592
01:16:37,896 --> 01:16:40,724
their own little
"piece of the pole,"

1593
01:16:40,793 --> 01:16:43,517
wanting it for themselves,

1594
01:16:43,586 --> 01:16:45,448
it's been lost.

1595
01:16:45,517 --> 01:16:48,241
There is only one hope.

1596
01:16:48,310 --> 01:16:51,413
It's going to take everyone
believing with me.

1597
01:16:51,482 --> 01:16:54,931
Everyone who has
a piece of the north pole,

1598
01:16:55,000 --> 01:16:57,689
you have to get
your piece of the north pole

1599
01:16:57,758 --> 01:16:59,655
and put it in your hand,

1600
01:16:59,724 --> 01:17:04,379
and you have to believe
very hard.

1601
01:17:04,448 --> 01:17:06,344
You have to believe

1602
01:17:06,413 --> 01:17:09,482
with everything
you have in you.

1603
01:17:09,551 --> 01:17:11,551
You have to believe
in the north pole

1604
01:17:11,620 --> 01:17:14,172
and Santa claus and Christmas.

1605
01:17:14,241 --> 01:17:22,206
You have to close your eyes
and see with your heart,

1606
01:17:22,275 --> 01:17:25,482
and maybe a miracle
will happen.

1607
01:17:25,551 --> 01:17:28,379
Believe.

1608
01:17:28,448 --> 01:17:31,689
Believe...

1609
01:17:31,758 --> 01:17:37,206
Believe...

1610
01:17:37,275 --> 01:17:39,034
Believe...

1611
01:17:39,103 --> 01:17:44,206
Believe...

1612
01:17:44,275 --> 01:17:46,379
Believe very hard.

1613
01:17:48,896 --> 01:17:52,620
Believe with me...

1614
01:17:52,689 --> 01:17:55,241
Believe with all your heart...

1615
01:18:01,413 --> 01:18:02,965
Thank you.

1616
01:18:06,103 --> 01:18:09,793
She's the world's
most incredible person,

1617
01:18:09,862 --> 01:18:12,344
and she loves me,

1618
01:18:12,413 --> 01:18:16,448
and I'm sitting here
wondering about what?

1619
01:18:16,517 --> 01:18:18,586
This doesn't matter.

1620
01:18:18,655 --> 01:18:19,551
'Cause we're going to get
through this,

1621
01:18:19,620 --> 01:18:21,206
no matter what,

1622
01:18:21,275 --> 01:18:22,241
because we're all
going to have each other,

1623
01:18:22,310 --> 01:18:24,241
and that's what matters.

1624
01:18:24,310 --> 01:18:26,448
That's the only thing
that counts.

1625
01:18:33,241 --> 01:18:37,827
Okay...

1626
01:18:37,896 --> 01:18:39,965
I believe.

1627
01:18:48,896 --> 01:18:49,827
Bill!

1628
01:18:49,896 --> 01:18:50,379
Daddy!

1629
01:18:50,448 --> 01:18:51,965
Dad!

1630
01:18:54,724 --> 01:18:56,275
Oh, guys!

1631
01:18:56,344 --> 01:19:00,172
I'm sorry
I didn't believe before,

1632
01:19:00,241 --> 01:19:01,655
but I do now.

1633
01:19:01,724 --> 01:19:04,413
I believe in you,
and in US, and in this,

1634
01:19:04,482 --> 01:19:05,586
more than I ever
thought I possibly could.

1635
01:19:05,655 --> 01:19:06,896
I know you do.

1636
01:19:06,965 --> 01:19:09,724
You couldn't have gotten here
if you didn't.

1637
01:19:12,344 --> 01:19:14,689
Well, nice try, Kristin.

1638
01:19:14,758 --> 01:19:16,241
Too bad it didn't work.

1639
01:19:16,310 --> 01:19:19,034
Bill...

1640
01:19:19,103 --> 01:19:22,931
This is my sister, rudolfa.

1641
01:19:23,000 --> 01:19:27,068
Are you kidding?

1642
01:19:27,137 --> 01:19:28,689
It's nice
to meet you.

1643
01:19:31,413 --> 01:19:33,172
Hey, look.

1644
01:19:41,655 --> 01:19:42,620
What is it?

1645
01:19:42,689 --> 01:19:44,034
The pieces
of the pole.

1646
01:19:44,103 --> 01:19:45,068
They're
coming home.

1647
01:20:04,655 --> 01:20:05,862
No, no, no, no!

1648
01:20:51,724 --> 01:20:54,482
Oh, no, no, no, no!
I don't believe this!

1649
01:20:54,551 --> 01:20:56,862
When am I ever going to
catch a break?

1650
01:21:07,586 --> 01:21:09,172
Kristin!

1651
01:21:09,241 --> 01:21:11,896
What happened?

1652
01:21:11,965 --> 01:21:15,103
We don't even have time
to tell you right now, dad.

1653
01:21:15,172 --> 01:21:16,379
Christmas is saved.

1654
01:21:16,448 --> 01:21:18,000
You have to
get going.

1655
01:21:21,241 --> 01:21:23,137
Well, this is
wonderful!

1656
01:21:25,310 --> 01:21:26,620
Even better.

1657
01:21:26,689 --> 01:21:29,103
Rudolfa!

1658
01:21:29,172 --> 01:21:30,689
The reindeer
aren't back yet.

1659
01:21:30,758 --> 01:21:32,655
I know.

1660
01:21:32,724 --> 01:21:35,000
I'll go get in the harness.

1661
01:21:39,965 --> 01:21:42,137
I thought I burnt this.

1662
01:21:42,206 --> 01:21:45,896
Merry Christmas, dad.

1663
01:21:45,965 --> 01:21:50,551
It will be now--
a merry Christmas for US all.

1664
01:21:50,620 --> 01:21:51,896
You've done it, Kristin.

1665
01:21:51,965 --> 01:21:57,034
Dad, this is bill.

1666
01:21:57,103 --> 01:21:58,827
Hello, bill.

1667
01:21:58,896 --> 01:22:00,551
Welcome to the family.

1668
01:22:00,620 --> 01:22:03,000
Thank you, Santa.

1669
01:22:03,068 --> 01:22:06,068
I just said that,
didn't I?

1670
01:22:06,137 --> 01:22:07,965
Quickly!
Help me fill up the sleigh.

1671
01:22:08,034 --> 01:22:09,931
We've got the presents
in the present room.

1672
01:22:10,000 --> 01:22:11,655
Come on, let's go.

1673
01:22:14,241 --> 01:22:16,137
[ Santa ]: Merry Christmas!

1674
01:22:19,206 --> 01:22:21,137
Lead the way, rudolfa.

1675
01:22:25,034 --> 01:22:27,137
Merry Christmas!

1676
01:22:29,862 --> 01:22:32,724
You have committed
to each other

1677
01:22:32,793 --> 01:22:34,103
to share,

1678
01:22:34,172 --> 01:22:35,103
to listen,

1679
01:22:35,172 --> 01:22:36,586
to love.

1680
01:22:36,655 --> 01:22:40,655
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

1681
01:23:38,275 --> 01:23:40,413
Do you want to make
these introductions

1682
01:23:40,482 --> 01:23:42,310
or should I?

1683
01:23:42,379 --> 01:23:43,827
Maybe both of US.

1684
01:23:43,896 --> 01:23:45,724
Together.

1685
01:23:48,068 --> 01:23:49,862
Mom, dad?

1686
01:23:49,931 --> 01:23:51,137
Come here.

1687
01:23:51,206 --> 01:23:53,965
I want you
to meet someone.

1688
01:23:54,034 --> 01:23:55,862
These are
Kristin's parents.

1689
01:23:55,931 --> 01:23:57,586
Hamilton and Joan,

1690
01:23:57,655 --> 01:23:59,655
this is my father,
Santa claus,

1691
01:23:59,724 --> 01:24:02,137
and my mom,
Clara claus.

1692
01:24:02,206 --> 01:24:02,724
Hi.

1693
01:24:02,793 --> 01:24:03,689
Hello.

1694
01:24:03,758 --> 01:24:05,896
Very pleased to meet you, Santa.

1695
01:24:05,965 --> 01:24:10,034
Pleasure to meet you, Hamilton.

1696
01:24:10,103 --> 01:24:13,896
That's a very pretty dress
you're wearing, Clara.

1697
01:24:13,965 --> 01:24:15,448
Thank you.
I've had it forever.

1698
01:24:15,517 --> 01:24:18,068
Oh.

1699
01:24:23,241 --> 01:24:25,034
So...

1700
01:24:25,103 --> 01:24:27,034
Why don't we go eat?

1701
01:24:27,103 --> 01:24:29,517
Sounds like a good idea.

1702
01:24:29,586 --> 01:24:31,137
I have a complaint.

1703
01:24:31,206 --> 01:24:32,586
I didn't get
what I wanted

1704
01:24:32,655 --> 01:24:35,724
for Christmas
this year, Santa.

1705
01:24:35,793 --> 01:24:37,862
Well, don't be
too surprised.

1706
01:24:37,931 --> 01:24:39,551
You weren't
very nice this year...

1707
01:24:39,620 --> 01:24:41,482
Not very nice at all,
I'm afraid.

1708
01:24:41,551 --> 01:24:43,620
What do you mean by that?

1709
01:24:43,689 --> 01:24:45,931
Now, dad...

1710
01:24:46,000 --> 01:24:47,724
Well, he asked me.

1711
01:24:47,793 --> 01:24:49,206
The man comes
to his own daughter's wedding

1712
01:24:49,275 --> 01:24:50,586
dressed in a Santa suit.

1713
01:24:50,655 --> 01:24:51,724
What is that?

1714
01:24:51,793 --> 01:24:53,241
Some kind
of a joke?

1715
01:24:53,310 --> 01:24:55,000
I assure you, sir, it is not.

1716
01:24:55,068 --> 01:24:57,551
I don't think I like your tone.

1717
01:24:57,620 --> 01:24:58,724
It's people like you

1718
01:24:58,793 --> 01:24:59,724
that make my job
so difficult.

1719
01:24:59,793 --> 01:25:01,413
People like me?

1720
01:25:01,482 --> 01:25:02,793
You don't even know
people like me, I'm sure.

1721
01:25:02,862 --> 01:25:04,310
Dad...

1722
01:25:04,379 --> 01:25:06,517
Can talk
about this later?

1723
01:25:06,586 --> 01:25:11,344
Well, now,
isn't this going to be fun?

1724
01:25:11,413 --> 01:25:13,413
We could all
do better.

1725
01:25:13,482 --> 01:25:16,586
That's what I meant.

1726
01:25:16,655 --> 01:25:18,689
Thank you.

1727
01:25:18,758 --> 01:25:19,793
Ahem.

1728
01:25:21,758 --> 01:25:25,275
Yes, well, I suppose we could.

1729
01:25:25,344 --> 01:25:27,034
Come on, dear.

1730
01:25:29,655 --> 01:25:32,862
How about a final photo
with your favorite uncle?

1731
01:25:40,344 --> 01:25:41,551
You okay?

1732
01:25:41,620 --> 01:25:42,620
Yeah.

1733
01:25:44,137 --> 01:25:46,137
This is our best
Christmas ever.

1734
01:25:46,206 --> 01:25:48,206
Merry Christmas to all of US

1735
01:25:48,275 --> 01:25:50,344
and for all the Christmas's
to come.

